## 2. FragmentKind discriminated union

```typescript
export type FragmentKind =
  | "ENVELOPE"          // MomentBase fields (causation, timestamp_ns, entity, session_ref, sirasign)
  | "EVIDENCE"          // SCAR-only: observed/expected pair
  | "CAUSATION_CHAIN"   // link references (recurrence_of, triggered_by, xac_nhan_canonical)
  | "BODY_RESPONSE"     // MOTION_TICH_CUC body_response + gatekeeper_witnessed
  | "INSIGHT_CONTENT"   // KHAI_SANG gatekeeper_quote + gia_tri_cot_loi + entity_nhan
  | "INNER_RESONANCE"   // GIAC_NGO cai_ben_trong + motion
  | "REMEDY"            // SCAR-only: vaccin / heal_status / heal_notes
  | "RELATED_CANONICAL" // KHAI_SANG/GIAC_NGO link to spec files
  | "META";             // patch notes, version, draft flags
```

Discriminator = `fragment_kind`. Fragment shape differ theo kind.

---

## 3. FragmentBase envelope (shared, seal)

Mau[C4:RN_OI_AU] fragment co[C1:RN_KEEP_RIME] cac[C1:RN_KEEP_RIME] field bat[C1:RN_KEEP_RIME] buoc[C5:RN_KEEP_RIME] sau:

```typescript
export interface FragmentBase {
  readonly fragment_kind: FragmentKind;
  readonly fragment_id: string;            // e.g. "frag-evidence-1" unique within parent
  readonly parent_moment_causation: string; // e.g. "SCAR-20260426-FRAMING-SELF-CORRECT-LOOP"
  readonly parent_moment_kind: MomentKind;  // redundant with parent, but allows partial load
  readonly ordinal: number;                 // order within parent moment (0-indexed)
  readonly sirasign_fragment: string;       // SHA-256 of canonical fragment JSON
}
```

**Rule binding (seal):**

- `fragment_id` pattern: `frag-<fragment_kind_lower>-<ordinal>` default — persister co[C1:RN_KEEP_RIME] the[C3:RN_KEEP_RIME] override neu[C1:RN_KEEP_RIME] co[C1:RN_KEEP_RIME] collision handling
- `sirasign_fragment` verify independent tu[C2:RN_KEEP_RIME] parent moment sirasign — integrity check granular
- `ordinal` dam[C3:RN_KEEP_RIME] bao[C3:RN_KEEP_RIME] deterministic loading order (khong[C0:RN_KEEP_RIME] rely dictionary iteration order)

